Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix
Date:                    2026-03-20
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + still image parameters + SSIM/CQP fix
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Three changes on top of the original build fix:
                         1. Still image mode: pred_structure=1 (low delay),
                            hierarchical_levels=0 (mini-gop=1), intra_period_length=-1,
                            fps=1/1. avif=true alone is insufficient in SVT-AV1 4.0.1.
                         2. tune=SSIM fallback: SVT-AV1 4.0.1 requires CRF for SSIM,
                            but libheif uses CQP. When sharp passes tune=ssim (its
                            default for .heif()), silently fall back to PSNR instead
                            of crashing with "tune SSIM only supports CRF".

--- libheif-1.21.2.orig/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-20 14:51:57.243826701 +0000
+++ libheif-1.21.2/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-20 14:52:08.491981564 +0000
@@ -829,8 +829,16 @@ static heif_error svt_start_sequence_enc
   svt_config.tile_columns = int_log2(encoder->tile_cols);
 
 #if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(0, 9, 1)
+  // SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0: tune=SSIM requires CRF rate control mode.
+  // libheif uses CQP (rate_control_mode=0), so fall back to PSNR to avoid encoder error.
+#if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(4, 0, 0)
+  svt_config.tune = (encoder->tune == encoder_struct_svt::Tune_SSIM)
+                    ? encoder_struct_svt::Tune_PSNR
+                    : encoder->tune;
+#else
   svt_config.tune = encoder->tune;
 #endif
+#endif
 
   svt_config.enc_mode = (int8_t) encoder->speed;
 
@@ -838,8 +846,20 @@ static heif_error svt_start_sequence_enc
     // svt_config.force_key_frames = true; TODO: this does not seem to work (see all [1])
 
